function vd(e) {

function Vy(e, t, n) {
    let {reference: r, floating: s} = e;
    const i = na(t)
      , l = Jg(t)
      , o = Xg(l)
      , c = hs(t)
      , u = i === "y"
      , d = r.x + r.width / 2 - s.width / 2
      , f = r.y + r.height / 2 - s.height / 2
      , m = r[o] / 2 - s[o] / 2;
    let h;
    switch (c) {
    case "top":
        h = {
            x: d,
            y: r.y - s.height
        };
        break;
    case "bottom":
        h = {
            x: d,
            y: r.y + r.height
        };
        break;
    case "right":
        h = {
            x: r.x + r.width,
            y: f
        };
        break;
    case "left":
        h = {
            x: r.x - s.width,
            y: f
        };
        break;
    default:
        h = {
            x: r.x,
            y: r.y
        }
    }
    switch (El(t)) {
    case "start":
        h[l] -= m * (n && u ? -1 : 1);
        break;
    case "end":
        h[l] += m * (n && u ? -1 : 1);
        break
    }
    return h
}

function hF(e, t) {
    const n = Math.abs(t.top - e.y)
      , r = Math.abs(t.bottom - e.y)
      , s = Math.abs(t.right - e.x)
      , i = Math.abs(t.left - e.x);
    switch (Math.min(n, r, s, i)) {
    case i:
        return "left";
    case s:
        return "right";
    case n:
        return "top";
    case r:
        return "bottom";
    default:
        throw new Error("unreachable")
    }
}
function pF(e, t, n=5) {
    const r = [];
    switch (t) {
    case "top":
        r.push({
            x: e.x - n,
            y: e.y + n
        }, {
            x: e.x + n,
            y: e.y + n
        });
        break;
    case "bottom":
        r.push({
            x: e.x - n,
            y: e.y - n
        }, {
            x: e.x + n,
            y: e.y - n
        });
        break;
    case "left":
        r.push({
            x: e.x + n,
            y: e.y - n
        }, {
            x: e.x + n,
            y: e.y + n
        });
        break;
    case "right":
        r.push({
            x: e.x - n,
            y: e.y - n
        }, {
            x: e.x - n,
            y: e.y + n
        });
        break
    }
    return r
}
function gF(e) {
    const {top: t, right: n, bottom: r, left: s} = e;
    return [{
        x: s,
        y: t
    }, {
        x: n,
        y: t
    }, {
        x: n,
        y: r
    }, {
        x: s,
        y: r
    }]
}
function xF(e, t) {
    const {x: n, y: r} = e;
    let s = !1;
    for (let i = 0, l = t.length - 1; i < t.length; l = i++) {
        const o = t[i].x
          , c = t[i].y
          , u = t[l].x
          , d = t[l].y;
        c > r != d > r && n < (u - o) * (r - c) / (d - c) + o && (s = !s)
    }
    return s
}
function vF(e) {
    const t = e.slice();
    return t.sort( (n, r) => n.x < r.x ? -1 : n.x > r.x ? 1 : n.y < r.y ? -1 : n.y > r.y ? 1 : 0),
    yF(t)
}
function yF(e) {
    if (e.length <= 1)
        return e.slice();
    const t = [];
    for (let r = 0; r < e.length; r++) {
        const s = e[r];
        for (; t.length >= 2; ) {
            const i = t[t.length - 1]
              , l = t[t.length - 2];
            if ((i.x - l.x) * (s.y - l.y) >= (i.y - l.y) * (s.x - l.x))
                t.pop();
            else
                break
        }
        t.push(s)
    }
    t.pop();
    const n = [];
    for (let r = e.length - 1; r >= 0; r--) {
        const s = e[r];
        for (; n.length >= 2; ) {
            const i = n[n.length - 1]
              , l = n[n.length - 2];

function d3(e) {

}
function h3(e, t) {

        c > r != d > r && n < (u - o) * (r - c) / (d - c) + o && (s = !s)

}

function Tp(e, [t,n]) {
    return Math.min(n, Math.max(t, e))

function PP(e) {

        value: e,
        previous: e
    });

    t.current.value = e),
    t.current.previous), [e])
}

var EP = "SelectTrigger"
  , RP = p.forwardRef( (e, t) => {

      , i = Vf(n)
      , l = fa(EP, n)
      , o = l.disabled || r
      , c = Ge(t, l.onTriggerChange)
      , u = Bf(n)
      , d = p.useRef("touch")
      , [f,m,h] = tM(y => {
        const b = u().filter(w => !w.disabled)
          , x = b.find(w => w.value === l.value)
          , v = nM(b, y, x);
        v !== void 0 && l.onValueChange(v.value)
    }
    )
      , g = y => {
        o || (l.onOpenChange(!0),
        h()),

            x: Math.round(y.pageX),
            y: Math.round(y.pageY)
        })
    }
    ;
    return a.jsx(ix, {
        asChild: !0,
        ...i,
        children: a.jsx(Me.button, {
            type: "button",

            "aria-required": l.required,
            "aria-autocomplete": "none",
            dir: l.dir,
            "data-state": l.open ? "open" : "closed",
            disabled: o,
            "data-disabled": o ? "" : void 0,
            "data-placeholder": JP(l.value) ? "" : void 0,
            ...s,
            ref: c,
            onClick: se(s.onClick, y => {
                y.currentTarget.focus(),

            }

const vl = (e, t) => {
    let n;
    switch (e.code) {
    case X.invalid_type:
        e.received === fe.undefined ? n = "Required" : n = `Expected ${e.expected}, received ${e.received}`;
        break;
    case X.invalid_literal:
        n = `Invalid literal value, expected ${JSON.stringify(e.expected, Ze.jsonStringifyReplacer)}`;
        break;
    case X.unrecognized_keys:
        n = `Unrecognized key(s) in object: ${Ze.joinValues(e.keys, ", ")}`;
        break;
    case X.invalid_union:
        n = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case X.invalid_union_discriminator:
        n = `Invalid discriminator value. Expected ${Ze.joinValues(e.options)}`;
        break;
    case X.invalid_enum_value:
        n = `Invalid enum value. Expected ${Ze.joinValues(e.options)}, received '${e.received}'`;
        break;
    case X.invalid_arguments:
        n = "Invalid function arguments";
        break;
    case X.invalid_return_type:
        n = "Invalid function return type";
        break;
    case X.invalid_date:
        n = "Invalid date";
        break;
    case X.invalid_string:
        typeof e.validation == "object" ? "includes"in e.validation ? (n = `Invalid input: must include "${e.validation.includes}"`,

        break;
    case X.too_small:
        e.type === "array" ? n = `Array must contain ${e.exact ? "exactly" : e.inclusive ? "at least" : "more than"} ${e.minimum} element(s)` : e.type === "string" ? n = `String must contain ${e.exact ? "exactly" : e.inclusive ? "at least" : "over"} ${e.minimum} character(s)` : e.type === "number" ? n = `Number must be ${e.exact ? "exactly equal to " : e.inclusive ? "greater than or equal to " : "greater than "}${e.minimum}` : e.type === "date" ? n = `Date must be ${e.exact ? "exactly equal to " : e.inclusive ? "greater than or equal to " : "greater than "}${new Date(Number(e.minimum))}` : n = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case X.too_big:
        e.type === "array" ? n = `Array must contain ${e.exact ? "exactly" : e.inclusive ? "at most" : "under"} ${e.maximum} character(s)` : e.type === "number" ? n = `Number must be ${e.exact ? "exactly" : e.inclusive ?         break;
    case X.custom:
        n = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case X.invalid_intersection_types:

    case X.not_multiple_of:

      , i = parseInt(e.toFixed(s).replace(".", ""))

    return i % l / Math.pow(10, s)
}
class sa extends We {
    constructor() {
        super(...arguments),
        this.min = this.gte,
        this.max = this.lte,
        this.step = this.multipleOf
    }
    _parse(t) {
        if (this._def.coerce && (t.data = Number(t.data)),
        this._getType(t) !== fe.number) {
            const i = this._getOrReturnCtx(t);
            return ce(i, {
                code: X.invalid_type,
                expected: fe.number,
                received: i.parsedType
            }),
            Ae
        }
        let r;
        const s = new dn;
        for (const i of this._def.checks)
            i.kind === "int" ? Ze.isInteger(t.data) || (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            ce(r, {
                code: X.invalid_type,
                expected: "integer",
                received: "float",
                message: i.message
            }),
            s.dirty()) : i.kind === "min" ? (i.inclusive ? t.data < i.value : t.data <= i.value) && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            ce(r, {
                code: X.too_small,
                minimum: i.value,
                type: "number",
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                exact: !1,
                message: i.message
            }),
            s.dirty()) : i.kind === "max" ? (i.inclusive ? t.data > i.value : t.data >= i.value) && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            ce(r, {
                code: X.too_big,
                maximum: i.value,
                type: "number",
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                exact: !1,
                message: i.message
            }),
            s.dirty()) : i.kind === "multipleOf" ? zz(t.data, i.value) !== 0 && (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            ce(r, {
                code: X.not_multiple_of,
                multipleOf: i.value,
                message: i.message
            }),
            s.dirty()) : i.kind === "finite" ? Number.isFinite(t.data) || (r = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, r),
            ce(r, {
                code: X.not_finite,
                message: i.message
            }),
            s.dirty()) : Ze.assertNever(i);
        return {
            status: s.value,
            value: t.data
        }
    }
    gte(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("min", t, !0, Ce.toString(n))
    }
    gt(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("min", t, !1, Ce.toString(n))
    }
    lte(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("max", t, !0, Ce.toString(n))
    }
    lt(t, n) {
        return this.setLimit("max", t, !1, Ce.toString(n))
    }
    setLimit(t, n, r, s) {
        return new sa({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, {
                kind: t,
                value: n,
                inclusive: r,
                message: Ce.toString(s)
            }]
        })
    }
    _addCheck(t) {
        return new sa({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, t]
        })
    }
    int(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "int",
            message: Ce.toString(t)
        })
    }
    positive(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ce.toString(t)
        })
    }
    negative(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ce.toString(t)
        })
    }
    nonpositive(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ce.toString(t)
        })
    }
    nonnegative(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ce.toString(t)
        })
    }
    multipleOf(t, n) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "multipleOf",
            value: t,
            message: Ce.toString(n)
        })
    }
    finite(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "finite",
            message: Ce.toString(t)
        })
    }
    safe(t) {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            inclusive: !0,
            value: Number.MIN_SAFE_INTEGER,
            message: Ce.toString(t)
        })._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            inclusive: !0,
            value: Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER,
            message: Ce.toString(t)
        })
    }
    get minValue() {
        let t = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks)
            n.kind === "min" && (t === null || n.value > t) && (t = n.value);
        return t
    }
    get maxValue() {
        let t = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks)
            n.kind === "max" && (t === null || n.value < t) && (t = n.value);
        return t
    }
    get isInt() {
        return !!this._def.checks.find(t => t.kind === "int" || t.kind === "multipleOf" && Ze.isInteger(t.value))
    }
    get isFinite() {
        let t = null
          , n = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks) {
            if (r.kind === "finite" || r.kind === "int" || r.kind === "multipleOf")
                return !0;
            r.kind === "min" ? (n === null || r.value > n) && (n = r.value) : r.kind === "max" && (t === null || r.value < t) && (t = r.value)
        }
        return Number.isFinite(n) && Number.isFinite(t)
    }
}

    ...ze(e)

class Ya extends We {
    _parse(t) {

        this._getType(t) !== fe.date) {

            }),

        }

            }),

        }

            i.kind === "min" ? t.data.getTime() < i.value && (s = this._getOrReturnCtx(t, s),

class wr extends We {
    _parse(t) {
        const {ctx: n, status: r} = this._processInputParams(t)
          , s = this._def;
        if (n.parsedType !== fe.array)
            return ce(n, {
                code: X.invalid_type,
                expected: fe.array,
                received: n.parsedType
            }),
            Ae;
        if (s.exactLength !== null) {
            const l = n.data.length > s.exactLength.value
              , o = n.data.length < s.exactLength.value;
            (l || o) && (ce(n, {
                code: l ? X.too_big : X.too_small,
                minimum: o ? s.exactLength.value : void 0,
                maximum: l ? s.exactLength.value : void 0,
                type: "array",
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !0,
                message: s.exactLength.message
            }),
            r.dirty())
        }
        if (s.minLength !== null && n.data.length < s.minLength.value && (ce(n, {
            code: X.too_small,
            minimum: s.minLength.value,
            type: "array",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: s.minLength.message
        }),
        r.dirty()),
        s.maxLength !== null && n.data.length > s.maxLength.value && (ce(n, {
            code: X.too_big,
            maximum: s.maxLength.value,
            type: "array",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: s.maxLength.message
        }),
        r.dirty()),
        n.common.async)
            return Promise.all([...n.data].map( (l, o) => s.type._parseAsync(new Hr(n,l,n.path,o)))).then(l => dn.mergeArray(r, l));
        const i = [...n.data].map( (l, o) => s.type._parseSync(new Hr(n,l,n.path,o)));
        return dn.mergeArray(r, i)
    }
    get element() {
        return this._def.type
    }
    min(t, n) {
        return new wr({
            ...this._def,
            minLength: {
                value: t,
                message: Ce.toString(n)
            }
        })
    }
    max(t, n) {
        return new wr({
            ...this._def,
            maxLength: {
                value: t,
                message: Ce.toString(n)
            }
        })
    }
    length(t, n) {
        return new wr({
            ...this._def,
            exactLength: {
                value: t,
                message: Ce.toString(n)
            }
        })
    }
    nonempty(t) {
        return this.min(1, t)
    }
}

    exactLength: null,
    typeName: _e.ZodArray,

function xi(e) {
    if (e instanceof yt) {
        const t = {};
        for (const n in e.shape) {
            const r = e.shape[n];
            t[n] = Ur.create(xi(r))
        }
        return new yt({
            ...e._def,
            shape: () => t
        })
    } else
        return e instanceof wr ? new wr({
            ...e._def,
            type: xi(e.element)
        }) : e instanceof Ur ? Ur.create(xi(e.unwrap())) : e instanceof la ? la.create(xi(e.unwrap())) : e instanceof Kr ? Kr.create(e.items.map(t => xi(t))) : e
}
class yt extends We {
    constructor() {
        super(...arguments),
        this._cached = null,
        this.nonstrict = this.passthrough,
        this.augment = this.extend
    }
    _getCached() {
        if (this._cached !== null)
            return this._cached;
        const t = this._def.shape()
          , n = Ze.objectKeys(t);
        return this._cached = {
            shape: t,
            keys: n
        }
    }
    _parse(t) {
        if (this._getType(t) !== fe.object) {
            const u = this._getOrReturnCtx(t);
            return ce(u, {
                code: X.invalid_type,
                expected: fe.object,
                received: u.parsedType
            }),
            Ae
        }
        const {status: r, ctx: s} = this._processInputParams(t)
          , {shape: i, keys: l} = this._getCached()
          , o = [];
        if (!(this._def.catchall instanceof ps && this._def.unknownKeys === "strip"))
            for (const u in s.data)
                l.includes(u) || o.push(u);
        const c = [];
        for (const u of l) {
            const d = i[u]
              , f = s.data[u];
            c.push({
                key: {
                    status: "valid",
                    value: u
                },
                value: d._parse(new Hr(s,f,s.path,u)),
                alwaysSet: u in s.data
            })
        }
        if (this._def.catchall instanceof ps) {
            const u = this._def.unknownKeys;
            if (u === "passthrough")
                for (const d of o)
                    c.push({
                        key: {
                            status: "valid",
                            value: d
                        },
                        value: {
                            status: "valid",
                            value: s.data[d]
                        }
                    });
            else if (u === "strict")
                o.length > 0 && (ce(s, {
                    code: X.unrecognized_keys,
                    keys: o
                }),
                r.dirty());
            else if (u !== "strip")
                throw new Error("Internal ZodObject error: invalid unknownKeys value.")
        } else {
            const u = this._def.catchall;
            for (const d of o) {
                const f = s.data[d];
                c.push({
                    key: {
                        status: "valid",
                        value: d
                    },
                    value: u._parse(new Hr(s,f,s.path,d)),
                    alwaysSet: d in s.data
                })
            }
        }
        return s.common.async ? Promise.resolve().then(async () => {
            const u = [];
            for (const d of c) {
                const f = await d.key
                  , m = await d.value;
                u.push({
                    key: f,
                    value: m,
                    alwaysSet: d.alwaysSet
                })
            }
            return u
        }
        ).then(u => dn.mergeObjectSync(r, u)) : dn.mergeObjectSync(r, c)
    }
    get shape() {
        return this._def.shape()
    }
    strict(t) {
        return Ce.errToObj,
        new yt({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "strict",
            ...t !== void 0 ? {
                errorMap: (n, r) => {
                    var s, i, l, o;
                    const c = (l = (i = (s = this._def).errorMap) === null || i === void 0 ? void 0 : i.call(s, n, r).message) !== null && l !== void 0 ? l : r.defaultError;
                    return n.code === "unrecognized_keys" ? {
                        message: (o = Ce.errToObj(t).message) !== null && o !== void 0 ? o : c
                    } : {
                        message: c
                    }
                }
            } : {}
        })
    }
    strip() {
        return new yt({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "strip"
        })
    }
    passthrough() {
        return new yt({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "passthrough"
        })
    }
    extend(t) {
        return new yt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => ({
                ...this._def.shape(),
                ...t
            })
        })
    }
    merge(t) {
        return new yt({
            unknownKeys: t._def.unknownKeys,
            catchall: t._def.catchall,
            shape: () => ({
                ...this._def.shape(),
                ...t._def.shape()
            }),
            typeName: _e.ZodObject
        })
    }
    setKey(t, n) {
        return this.augment({
            [t]: n
        })
    }
    catchall(t) {
        return new yt({
            ...this._def,
            catchall: t
        })
    }
    pick(t) {
        const n = {};
        return Ze.objectKeys(t).forEach(r => {
            t[r] && this.shape[r] && (n[r] = this.shape[r])
        }
        ),
        new yt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => n
        })
    }
    omit(t) {
        const n = {};
        return Ze.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(r => {
            t[r] || (n[r] = this.shape[r])
        }
        ),
        new yt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => n
        })
    }
    deepPartial() {
        return xi(this)
    }
    partial(t) {
        const n = {};
        return Ze.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(r => {
            const s = this.shape[r];
            t && !t[r] ? n[r] = s : n[r] = s.optional()
        }
        ),
        new yt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => n
        })
    }
    required(t) {
        const n = {};
        return Ze.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(r => {
            if (t && !t[r])
                n[r] = this.shape[r];
            else {
                let i = this.shape[r];
                for (; i instanceof Ur; )
                    i = i._def.innerType;
                n[r] = i
            }
        }
        ),
        new yt({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => n
        })
    }
    keyof() {
        return JM(Ze.objectKeys(this.shape))
    }
}

class Jo extends We {
    _parse(t) {

          , r = this._def.options;
        function s(i) {
            for (const o of i)
                if (o.result.status === "valid")
                    return o.result;
            for (const o of i)

                    return n.common.issues.push(...o.ctx.common.issues),
                    o.result;

                    },

                        data: n.data,
                        path: n.path,
                        parent: l
                    }),

                }

                        issues: []
                    },

                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: u
                });

            }),

        }
    }

class Gf extends We {
    _parse(t) {
        const {ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(t);
        if (n.parsedType !== fe.object)
            return ce(n, {
                code: X.invalid_type,
                expected: fe.object,
                received: n.parsedType
            }),
            Ae;
        const r = this.discriminator
          , s = n.data[r]
          , i = this.optionsMap.get(s);
        return i ? n.common.async ? i._parseAsync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }) : i._parseSync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }) : (ce(n, {
            code: X.invalid_union_discriminator,
            options: Array.from(this.optionsMap.keys()),
            path: [r]
        }),
        Ae)
    }

    }
    get options() {
        return this._def.options
    }

        return this._def.optionsMap
    }
    static create(t, n, r) {
        const s = new Map;
        for (const i of n) {
            const l = es(i.shape[t]);
            if (!l.length)
                throw new Error(`A discriminator value for key \`${t}\` could not be extracted from all schema options`);
            for (const o of l) {
                if (s.has(o))
                    throw new Error(`Discriminator property ${String(t)} has duplicate value ${String(o)}`);
                s.set(o, i)
            }
        }

            typeName: _e.ZodDiscriminatedUnion,

        })
    }

function Lp(e, t) {
    const n = rs(e)
      , r = rs(t);
    if (e === t)
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: e
        };
    if (n === fe.object && r === fe.object) {
        const s = Ze.objectKeys(t)
          , i = Ze.objectKeys(e).filter(o => s.indexOf(o) !== -1)
          , l = {
            ...e,
            ...t
        };
        for (const o of i) {
            const c = Lp(e[o], t[o]);
            if (!c.valid)
                return {
                    valid: !1
                };
            l[o] = c.data
        }
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: l
        }
    } else if (n === fe.array && r === fe.array) {
        if (e.length !== t.length)
            return {
                valid: !1
            };
        const s = [];
        for (let i = 0; i < e.length; i++) {
            const l = e[i]
              , o = t[i]
              , c = Lp(l, o);
            if (!c.valid)
                return {
                    valid: !1
                };
            s.push(c.data)
        }
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: s
        }
    } else
        return n === fe.date && r === fe.date && +e == +t ? {
            valid: !0,
            data: e
        } : {
            valid: !1
        }
}

class Qa extends We {
    _parse(t) {
        const {status: n, ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(t);

            }

                status: n.value,
                value: u
            }

            }

    }

    }

class ia extends We {

    }

        for (const n of this._def.values)
            t[n] = n;
        return t
    }

            ...this._def,

        })
    }

        })
    }

class Tr extends We {
    innerType() {
        return this._def.schema
    }
    sourceType() {
        return this._def.schema._def.typeName === _e.ZodEffects ? this._def.schema.sourceType() : this._def.schema
    }
    _parse(t) {
        const {status: n, ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(t)
          , s = this._def.effect || null
          , i = {
            addIssue: l => {
                ce(r, l),
                l.fatal ? n.abort() : n.dirty()
            }
            ,
            get path() {
                return r.path
            }
        };
        if (i.addIssue = i.addIssue.bind(i),
        s.type === "preprocess") {
            const l = s.transform(r.data, i);
            if (r.common.async)
                return Promise.resolve(l).then(async o => {
                    if (n.value === "aborted")
                        return Ae;
                    const c = await this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                        data: o,
                        path: r.path,
                        parent: r
                    });
                    return c.status === "aborted" ? Ae : c.status === "dirty" || n.value === "dirty" ? Ei(c.value) : c
                }
                );
            {
                if (n.value === "aborted")
                    return Ae;
                const o = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: l,
                    path: r.path,
                    parent: r
                });
                return o.status === "aborted" ? Ae : o.status === "dirty" || n.value === "dirty" ? Ei(o.value) : o
            }
        }
        if (s.type === "refinement") {
            const l = o => {
                const c = s.refinement(o, i);
                if (r.common.async)
                    return Promise.resolve(c);
                if (c instanceof Promise)
                    throw new Error("Async refinement encountered during synchronous parse operation. Use .parseAsync instead.");
                return o
            }
            ;
            if (r.common.async === !1) {
                const o = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: r.data,
                    path: r.path,
                    parent: r
                });
                return o.status === "aborted" ? Ae : (o.status === "dirty" && n.dirty(),
                l(o.value),
                {
                    status: n.value,
                    value: o.value
                })
            } else
                return this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                    data: r.data,
                    path: r.path,
                    parent: r
                }).then(o => o.status === "aborted" ? Ae : (o.status === "dirty" && n.dirty(),
                l(o.value).then( () => ({
                    status: n.value,
                    value: o.value
                }))))
        }
        if (s.type === "transform")
            if (r.common.async === !1) {
                const l = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: r.data,
                    path: r.path,
                    parent: r
                });
                if (!qa(l))
                    return l;
                const o = s.transform(l.value, i);
                if (o instanceof Promise)
                    throw new Error("Asynchronous transform encountered during synchronous parse operation. Use .parseAsync instead.");
                return {
                    status: n.value,
                    value: o
                }
            } else
                return this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                    data: r.data,
                    path: r.path,
                    parent: r
                }).then(l => qa(l) ? Promise.resolve(s.transform(l.value, i)).then(o => ({
                    status: n.value,
                    value: o
                })) : l);
        Ze.assertNever(s)
    }
}

function Ql(e) {

        const r = n.width
          , s = r && e.matchPatterns[r] || e.matchPatterns[e.defaultMatchWidth]
          , i = t.match(s);
        if (!i)
            return null;

          , o = r && e.parsePatterns[r] || e.parsePatterns[e.defaultParseWidth]
          , c = Array.isArray(o) ? pB(o, f => f.test(l)) : hB(o, f => f.test(l));

        u = n.valueCallback ? n.valueCallback(u) : u;

            value: u,
            rest: d
        }
    }
}

        l = n.valueCallback ? n.valueCallback(l) : l;
        const o = t.slice(s.length);
        return {
            value: l,
            rest: o
        }
    }
}

function lt(e, t) {

const Ns = {
    y(e, t) {
        const n = e.getFullYear()
          , r = n > 0 ? n : 1 - n;
        return lt(t === "yy" ? r % 100 : r, t.length)
    },
    M(e, t) {
        const n = e.getMonth();
        return t === "M" ? String(n + 1) : lt(n + 1, 2)
    },
    d(e, t) {
        return lt(e.getDate(), t.length)
    },
    a(e, t) {
        const n = e.getHours() / 12 >= 1 ? "pm" : "am";
        switch (t) {
        case "a":
        case "aa":
            return n.toUpperCase();
        case "aaa":
            return n;
        case "aaaaa":
            return n[0];
        case "aaaa":
        default:
            return n === "am" ? "a.m." : "p.m."
        }
    },
    h(e, t) {
        return lt(e.getHours() % 12 || 12, t.length)
    },
    H(e, t) {
        return lt(e.getHours(), t.length)
    },
    m(e, t) {
        return lt(e.getMinutes(), t.length)
    },
    s(e, t) {
        return lt(e.getSeconds(), t.length)
    },

        const n = t.length
          , r = e.getMilliseconds()
          , s = Math.trunc(r * Math.pow(10, n - 3));
        return lt(s, t.length)
    }
}

function Eb(e, t="") {

function PE(e, t) {

const xu = {

function eV(e, t) {
    const n = new RegExp("^(?:(\\d{4}|[+-]\\d{" + (4 + t) + "})|(\\d{2}|[+-]\\d{" + (2 + t) + "})$)")
      , r = e.match(n);

        return {
            year: NaN,
            restDateString: ""
        };

      , i = r[2] ? parseInt(r[2]) : null;

        year: i === null ? s : i * 100,
        restDateString: e.slice((r[1] || r[2]).length)
    }
}
function tV(e, t) {

        return new Date(NaN);

        u)
    }
}
function Zl(e) {

function nV(e) {

function Xm(e) {

function rV(e) {

function sV(e, t, n) {

const gV = H.object({
    templeName: H.string().min(2, "Temple name must be at least 2 characters"),
    deity: H.string().optional(),
    village: H.string().min(1, "Village is required"),
    nearestCity: H.string().min(1, "Nearest city is required"),
    state: H.string().min(1, "State is required"),
    country: H.string().min(1, "Country is required"),
    establishedYear: H.number().optional(),
    contactPhone: H.string().optional(),
    contactEmail: H.string().email("Please enter a valid email address").optional().or(H.literal("")),
    description: H.string().optional(),
    templeImage: H.string().optional()
});
function xV() {
    const {t: e} = Vt()
      , [t,n] = p.useState(null)
      , [r,s] = p.useState(!1)
      , [i,l] = p.useState(null)
      , [o,c] = p.useState(!1)
      , [u,d] = p.useState({
        members: [],
        title: "",
        description: ""
    })
      , {toast: f} = qr()
      , m = da()
      , {data: h=[]} = dt({
        queryKey: ["/api/members"]
    })
      , {data: g=[]} = dt({
        queryKey: ["/api/temples"]
    })
      , y = () => {
        if (t) {
            const O = h.filter(L => L.templeId === t.id).length;
            return {
                totalMembers: O,
                totalFamilies: Math.ceil(O / 3.6),
                annualEvents: 48,
                volunteers: Math.ceil(O * .125)
            }
        } else {
            const T = h.length;
            return {
                totalMembers: T,
                totalFamilies: Math.ceil(T / 3.6),
                annualEvents: 48,
                volunteers: Math.ceil(T * .125)
            }
        }
    }
      , {totalMembers: b, totalFamilies: x, annualEvents: v, volunteers: w} = y()
      , C = () => t ? h.filter(T => T.templeId === t.id) : h
      , j = () => {
        const T = C();
        d({
            members: T,
            title: t ? `${t.templeName} - All Members` : "All Registered Members",
            description: `Complete list of ${T.length} registered community members`
        }),
        c(!0)
    }
      , S = () => {
        const T = C().filter(O => O.maritalStatus === "Married");
        d({
            members: T,
            title: t ? `${t.templeName} - Married Members` : "Married Members",
            description: `${T.length} married community members and their families`
        }),
        c(!0)
    }
    ;
    p.useEffect( () => {
        t ? document.title = `${t.templeName} - Our Temple` : document.title = "Nam Kovil - Devine Portal"
    }
    , [t]);
    const N = Dc({
        resolver: Lc(gV),
        defaultValues: {
            templeName: "",
            deity: "",
            village: "",
            nearestCity: "",
            state: "",
            country: "",
            establishedYear: void 0,
            contactPhone: "",
            contactEmail: "",
            description: "",
            templeImage: ""
        }
    })
      , k = Mn({
        mutationFn: async T => {
            if (!t)
                throw new Error("No temple selected");
            return await cn("PUT", `/api/temples/${t.id}`, T)
        }
        ,
        onSuccess: () => {
            m.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/temples"]
            }),
            s(!1),
            f({
                title: "Temple Updated",
                description: "Temple details have been successfully updated."
            })
        }
        ,
        onError: T => {
            f({
                title: "Update Failed",
                description: T.message || "Failed to update temple details",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , M = T => {
        if (T === "reset") {
            n(null);
            return
        }
        const O = g.find(L => L.id.toString() === T);
        n(O || null)
    }
      , R = T => {
        var L;
        const O = (L = T.target.files) == null ? void 0 : L[0];
        if (O) {
            if (O.size > 5 * 1024 * 1024) {
                f({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "Image size must be less than 5MB",
                    variant: "destructive"
                });
                return
            }
            const q = new FileReader;
            q.onload = E => {
                var z;
                const D = (z = E.target) == null ? void 0 : z.result
                  , A = new Image;
                A.onload = () => {
                    const U = document.createElement("canvas")
                      , K = U.getContext("2d")
                      , W = 800;
                    let {width: ie, height: Se} = A;
                    ie > Se ? ie > W && (Se = Se * W / ie,
                    ie = W) : Se > W && (ie = ie * W / Se,
                    Se = W),
                    U.width = ie,
                    U.height = Se,
                    K == null || K.drawImage(A, 0, 0, ie, Se);
                    const Oe = U.toDataURL("image/jpeg", .8);
                    l(Oe),
                    N.setValue("templeImage", Oe)
                }
                ,
                A.src = D
            }
            ,
            q.readAsDataURL(O)
        }
    }

        t && k.mutate(T)

function Ab(e, t, n) {
    for (let r = t; r < e.length; r++) {
        const s = e[r];
        if (s === "\\") {
            r++;
            continue
        }
        if (s === '"')
            return [e.slice(t, r).replace(/\\/g, ""), r + 1];
        if (!n && (s === "," || s === "}"))
            return [e.slice(t, r).replace(/\\/g, ""), r]
    }
    return [e.slice(t).replace(/\\/g, ""), e.length]
}
function AE(e, t=0) {
    const n = [];
    let r = t
      , s = !1;
    for (; r < e.length; ) {
        const i = e[r];
        if (i === ",") {
            (s || r === t) && n.push(""),
            s = !0,
            r++;
            continue
        }
        if (s = !1,
        i === "\\") {
            r += 2;
            continue
        }
        if (i === '"') {
            const [c,u] = Ab(e, r + 1, !0);
            n.push(c),
            r = u;
            continue
        }
        if (i === "}")
            return [n, r + 1];
        if (i === "{") {
            const [c,u] = AE(e, r + 1);
            n.push(c),
            r = u;
            continue
        }
        const [l,o] = Ab(e, r, !1);
        n.push(l),
        r = o
    }
    return [n, r]
}

function GV(e) {
    const t = [];
    for (let n = 0; n < e.length; n += 2)
        t.push(Number.parseInt(e.slice(n, n + 2), 16));
    return new Uint8Array(t)
}
function Fb(e, t) {
    const n = new ArrayBuffer(8)
      , r = new DataView(n);
    for (let s = 0; s < 8; s++)
        r.setUint8(s, e[t + s]);
    return r.getFloat64(0, !0)
}
function D2(e) {
    const t = GV(e);
    let n = 0;
    const r = t[n];
    n += 1;
    const s = new DataView(t.buffer)
      , i = s.getUint32(n, r === 1);
    if (n += 4,
    i & 536870912 && (s.getUint32(n, r === 1),
    n += 4),
    (i & 65535) === 1) {
        const l = Fb(t, n);
        n += 8;
        const o = Fb(t, n);
        return n += 8,
        [l, o]
    }
    throw new Error("Unsupported geometry type")
}

var Wx = "Progress"
  , Gx = 100
  , [pU,nG] = Dn(Wx)
  , [gU,xU] = pU(Wx)
  , yR = p.forwardRef( (e, t) => {
    const {__scopeProgress: n, value: r=null, max: s, getValueLabel: i=vU, ...l} = e;
    (s || s === 0) && !zb(s) && console.error(yU(`${s}`, "Progress"));
    const o = zb(s) ? s : Gx;
    r !== null && !Bb(r, o) && console.error(bU(`${r}`, "Progress"));
    const c = Bb(r, o) ? r : null
      , u = Wd(c) ? i(c, o) : void 0;
    return a.jsx(gU, {
        scope: n,
        value: c,
        max: o,
        children: a.jsx(Me.div, {
            "aria-valuemax": o,
            "aria-valuemin": 0,
            "aria-valuenow": Wd(c) ? c : void 0,
            "aria-valuetext": u,
            role: "progressbar",
            "data-state": NR(c, o),
            "data-value": c ?? void 0,
            "data-max": o,
            ...l,
            ref: t
        })
    })
}
);
yR.displayName = Wx;
var bR = "ProgressIndicator"
  , wR = p.forwardRef( (e, t) => {
    const {__scopeProgress: n, ...r} = e
      , s = xU(bR, n);
    return a.jsx(Me.div, {

    })
}

wR.displayName = bR;
function vU(e, t) {
    return `${Math.round(e / t * 100)}%`
}
function NR(e, t) {
    return e == null ? "indeterminate" : e === t ? "complete" : "loading"
}
function Wd(e) {
    return typeof e == "number"
}
function zb(e) {
    return Wd(e) && !isNaN(e) && e > 0
}
function Bb(e, t) {
    return Wd(e) && !isNaN(e) && e <= t && e >= 0
}
function yU(e, t) {
    return `Invalid prop \`max\` of value \`${e}\` supplied to \`${t}\`. Only numbers greater than 0 are valid max values. Defaulting to \`${Gx}\`.`
}
function bU(e, t) {
    return `Invalid prop \`value\` of value \`${e}\` supplied to \`${t}\`. The \`value\` prop must be:
  - a positive number
  - less than the value passed to \`max\` (or ${Gx} if no \`max\` prop is set)
  - \`null\` or \`undefined\` if the progress is indeterminate.

Defaulting to \`null\`.`
}

  , wU = wR;

function SU() {
    const {t: e} = Vt()
      , [,t] = ni()
      , [n,r] = p.useState(!1)
      , [s,i] = p.useState("")
      , [l,o] = p.useState(null)
      , [c,u] = p.useState("")
      , [d,f] = p.useState([]);
    p.useState(null);
    const [m,h] = p.useState("")
      , [g,y] = p.useState("")
      , [b,x] = p.useState("")
      , [v,w] = p.useState("")
      , [C,j] = p.useState([])
      , [S,N] = p.useState("")
      , {toast: k} = qr()
      , M = da()
      , {data: R=[]} = dt({
        queryKey: ["/api/temples"]
    })
      , F = Dc({
        resolver: Lc(NU),
        defaultValues: {
            fullName: "",
            phone: "",
            email: "",
            gender: void 0,
            birthCity: "",
            birthState: "",
            birthCountry: "",
            currentCity: "",
            currentState: "",
            currentCountry: "",
            fatherName: "",
            motherName: "",
            spouseName: "",
            maritalStatus: "Single"
        }
    });
    dt({
        queryKey: ["/api/members/search", {
            term: s
        }],
        queryFn: async () => {
            if (!s || s.length < 2)
                return [];
            const E = await fetch(`/api/members/search?term=${encodeURIComponent(s)}`);
            return E.ok ? E.json() : []
        }
        ,
        enabled: s.length > 2
    });
    const T = Mn({
        mutationFn: async E => {
            const D = {
                ...E,
                templeId: v && v !== "none" ? parseInt(v) : null,
                profilePicture: S || void 0,
                photos: C
            };
            return delete D.selectedTemple,
            await cn("POST", "/api/members", D)
        }
        ,
        onSuccess: async E => {
            for (const {member: D, relationship: A} of d)
                await cn("POST", "/api/relationships", {
                    memberId: E.id,
                    relatedMemberId: D.id,
                    relationshipType: A
                });
            M.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/members"]
            }),
            r(!0),
            localStorage.removeItem("registry-form-draft"),
            F.reset({
                fullName: "",
                phone: "",
                email: "",
                gender: void 0,
                birthCity: "",
                birthState: "",
                birthCountry: "",
                currentCity: "",
                currentState: "",
                currentCountry: "",
                fatherName: "",
                motherName: "",
                spouseName: "",
                maritalStatus: "Single",
                selectedTemple: "",
                linkedRelatives: []
            }),

            o(null),
            u(""),
            h(""),
            y(""),
            x(""),
            w(""),
            j([]),

                title: "Registration Successful!",
                description: "Member has been registered and form has been cleared for next entry.",
                variant: "default"
            })
        }
        ,

                title: "Registration Failed",
                description: E.message || "Failed to register member",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , O = E => {
        localStorage.removeItem("registry-form-draft"),
        T.mutate(E)
    }
      , L = () => {

            ...E,
            linkedRelatives: d,
            timestamp: new Date().toISOString()
        }))
    }
    ;
    p.useEffect( () => {
        const E = localStorage.getItem("registry-form-draft");
        if (E)
            try {
                const D = JSON.parse(E);
                new Date().getTime() - new Date(D.timestamp).getTime() < 24 * 60 * 60 * 1e3 && (F.reset(D),
                f(D.linkedRelatives || []),
                h(D.maritalStatus || ""),
                y(D.birthCountry || ""),
                x(D.currentCountry || ""),
                w(D.selectedTemple || ""),
                k({
                    title: "Draft Restored",
                    description: "Your previously saved form data has been restored."
                }))
            } catch (D) {
                console.error("Error loading draft:", D)
            }
    }
    , [F, k]);

        r(!1),

    }

            ),

                y.current || C.stopPropagation())
            }
            )

var PU = e => {
    const {control: t, checked: n, bubbles: r=!0, defaultChecked: s, ...i} = e

      , o = PP(n)
      , c = YT(t);

          , f = window.HTMLInputElement.prototype
          , h = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(f, "checked").set;

                bubbles: r
            });
            d.indeterminate = Qs(n),
            h.call(d, Qs(n) ? !1 : n),

function Qs(e) {
    return e === "indeterminate"
}
function PR(e) {
    return Qs(e) ? "indeterminate" : e ? "checked" : "unchecked"

function qU() {
    const {t: e} = Vt()
      , [,t] = ni()
      , [n,r] = p.useState(!1)
      , [s,i] = p.useState([])
      , [l,o] = p.useState("")
      , [c,u] = p.useState(null)
      , [d,f] = p.useState([])
      , {toast: m} = qr()
      , h = da()
      , g = Dc({
        resolver: Lc(HU),
        defaultValues: {
            templeName: "",
            deity: "",
            village: "",
            nearestCity: "",
            state: "",
            country: "",
            linkedTemples: [],
            establishedYear: void 0,
            contactPhone: "",
            contactEmail: "",
            description: "",
            templeImage: "",
            templePhotos: [],
            googleMapLink: "",
            websiteLink: "",
            wikiLink: ""
        }
    })
      , {data: y=[]} = dt({
        queryKey: ["/api/temples"]
    })
      , b = Mn({
        mutationFn: async S => (await cn("POST", "/api/temples", {
            ...S,
            linkedTemples: s,
            establishedYear: S.establishedYear || void 0
        })).json(),
        onSuccess: () => {
            h.invalidateQueries({
                queryKey: ["/api/temples"]
            }),
            r(!0),
            m({
                title: e("common.success"),
                description: e("templeRegistry.success")
            })
        }
        ,
        onError: () => {
            m({
                title: e("common.error"),
                description: e("templeRegistry.error"),
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    })
      , x = S => {
        u(S),
        g.setValue("templeImage", S)
    }
      , v = S => {
        f(S),
        g.setValue("templePhotos", S)
    }
      , w = (S, N) => {
        i(N ? [...s, S] : s.filter(k => k !== S))
    }
      , C = S => {
        const N = {
            ...S,
            linkedTemples: s,
            templeImage: c || "",
            templePhotos: d
        };
        b.mutate(N)
    }
      , j = () => {
        r(!1),
        g.reset(),
        u(null),
        f([]),
        i([]),
        t("/temples")
    }
    ;

var Kx = "Tabs"
  , [QU,aG] = Dn(Kx, [Df])
  , QR = Df()
  , [ZU,qx] = QU(Kx)
  , ZR = p.forwardRef( (e, t) => {
    const {__scopeTabs: n, value: r, onValueChange: s, defaultValue: i, orientation: l="horizontal", dir: o, activationMode: c="automatic", ...u} = e
      , d = Mc(o)
      , [f,m] = Js({
        prop: r,
        onChange: s,
        defaultProp: i
    });
    return a.jsx(ZU, {
        scope: n,
        baseId: Br(),
        value: f,
        onValueChange: m,
        orientation: l,
        dir: d,
        activationMode: c,
        children: a.jsx(Me.div, {
            dir: d,
            "data-orientation": l,
            ...u,
            ref: t
        })

                strokeWidth: "3",
                className: "drop-shadow-lg hover:stroke-yellow-400 transition-all duration-300"
            });

                N && S.push(N);

                return S.map( (M, R) => a.jsx("text", {
                    x: h.position.x,

                    children: M
                }, `name-${R}`))
            }
            )(), !h.isCenter && ( () => {
                const j = i(h.relationshipType).split(" ")
                  , S = 8
                  , N = [];

                j.forEach(R => {
                    (k + " " + R).length <= S ? k = k ? k + " " + R : R : (k && N.push(k),
                    k = R.length > S ? R.substring(0, S - 2) + ".." : R)
                }
                ),
                k && N.push(k);
                const M = h.position.y - N.length * 5;

            )(), a.jsxs("g", {

    }
    ;
    return t.length === 0 ? a.jsxs(re, {

            })]
        }), a.jsx("div", {
            className: "w-full overflow-auto",
            children: a.jsxs("svg", {
                width: "100%",

                    }), a.jsx("filter", {

                            floodOpacity: "0.3"
                        })
                    })]
                }), a.jsx("rect", {
                    width: "100%",

                    fill: "url(#grid)"
                }), d(), u.map( (h, g) => m(h, g)), a.jsxs("g", {

                    children: [a.jsx("rect", {

function D8({allMembers: e, allRelationships: t, onMemberClick: n}) {
    const {t: r} = Vt();
    ha();
    const s = () => {
        const u = {}
          , d = []
          , f = new Set;
        t.forEach(h => {
            u[h.memberId] || (u[h.memberId] = new Set),
            u[h.relatedMemberId] || (u[h.relatedMemberId] = new Set),
            u[h.memberId].add(h.relatedMemberId),
            u[h.relatedMemberId].add(h.memberId)
        }
        );
        const m = h => {
            const g = []
              , y = [h]
              , b = new Set;
            for (; y.length > 0; ) {
                const x = y.shift();
                if (b.has(x))
                    continue;
                b.add(x),
                f.add(x);
                const v = e.find(C => C.id === x);
                v && g.push(v),
                (u[x] || new Set).forEach(C => {
                    b.has(C) || y.push(C)
                }
                )
            }
            return g
        }
        ;
        return e.forEach(h => {
            if (!f.has(h.id) && u[h.id]) {
                const g = m(h.id);
                if (g.length > 1) {
                    const y = [...new Set(g.map(b => `${b.currentCity}, ${b.currentState}`))];
                    d.push({
                        id: `cluster-${d.length}`,
                        members: g,
                        connections: g.reduce( (b, x) => {
                            var v;
                            return b + (((v = u[x.id]) == null ? void 0 : v.size) || 0)
                        }
                        , 0) / 2,
                        generations: i(g, t),
                        locations: y
                    })
                }
            }
        }
        ),
        d.sort( (h, g) => g.members.length - h.members.length)
    }
      , i = (u, d) => {
        const f = d.filter(h => u.some(g => g.id === h.memberId) && u.some(g => g.id === h.relatedMemberId));
        return new Set(f.map(h => {
            const g = h.relationshipType.toLowerCase();
            return ["grandfather", "grandmother"].includes(g) ? "grandparent" : ["father", "mother"].includes(g) ? "parent" : ["child"].includes(g) ? "child" : "same"
        }
        )).size
    }
      , l = () => {
        const u = {
            total: t.length,
            byType: {},
            mostConnected: null,
            avgConnections: 0
        };
        t.forEach(h => {
            u.byType[h.relationshipType] = (u.byType[h.relationshipType] || 0) + 1
        }
        );
        const d = {};
        t.forEach(h => {
            d[h.memberId] = (d[h.memberId] || 0) + 1
        }
        );
        let f = 0
          , m = 0;
        return Object.entries(d).forEach( ([h,g]) => {
            g > f && (f = g,
            m = parseInt(h))
        }
        ),
        u.mostConnected = e.find(h => h.id === m) || null,
        u.avgConnections = Object.values(d).reduce( (h, g) => h + g, 0) / Object.keys(d).length || 0,
        u
    }
      , o = s()
      , c = l();
    return a.jsxs("div", {
        className: "space-y-6",
        children: [a.jsxs("div", {
            className: "grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4",
            children: [a.jsxs(re, {
                className: "p-4 text-center bg-gradient-to-br from-saffron-50 to-gold-50",
                children: [a.jsx(wo, {
                    className: "mx-auto mb-2 text-saffron-600",
                    size: 24
                }), a.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-2xl font-bold text-temple-brown",
                    children: o.length
                }), a.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-sm text-gray-600",
                    children: r("familyTree.familyClusters", "Family Clusters")
                })]
            }), a.jsxs(re, {
                className: "p-4 text-center bg-gradient-to-br from-temple-light to-saffron-50",
                children: [a.jsx($e, {
                    className: "mx-auto mb-2 text-temple-brown",
                    size: 24
                }), a.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-2xl font-bold text-temple-brown",
                    children: c.total
                }), a.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-sm text-gray-600",
                    children: r("familyTree.totalConnections", "Total Connections")
                })]
            }), a.jsxs(re, {
                className: "p-4 text-center bg-gradient-to-br from-gold-50 to-yellow-50",
                children: [a.jsx(mO, {
                    className: "mx-auto mb-2 text-temple-gold",
                    size: 24
                }), a.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-2xl font-bold text-temple-brown",
                    children: c.avgConnections.toFixed(1)
                }), a.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-sm text-gray-600",
                    children: r("familyTree.avgConnections", "Avg Connections")
                })]
            }), a.jsxs(re, {
                className: "p-4 text-center bg-gradient-to-br from-temple-gold-50 to-saffron-50",
                children: [a.jsx(dd, {
                    className: "mx-auto mb-2 text-saffron-500",
                    size: 24
                }), a.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-2xl font-bold text-temple-brown",
                    children: Object.keys(c.byType).length
                }), a.jsx("div", {
                    className: "text-sm text-gray-600",
                    children: r("familyTree.relationshipTypes", "Relationship Types")
                })]
            })]
        }), c.mostConnected && a.jsx(re, {
            className: "p-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-saffron-500 to-gold-500 text-white",
            children: a.jsxs("div", {
                className: "flex items-center justify-between",
                children: [a.jsxs("div", {
                    children: [a.jsx("h3", {
                        className: "text-lg font-semibold mb-2",
                        children: r("familyTree.mostConnectedMember", "Most Connected Family Member")
                    }), a.jsx("p", {
                        className: "text-xl font-bold",
                        children: c.mostConnected.fullName
                    }), a.jsxs("p", {
                        className: "text-saffron-100 text-sm",
                        children: [Object.values(c.byType).reduce( (u, d) => Math.max(u, d), 0), " family connections"]
                    })]
                }), a.jsx(J, {
                    variant: "outline",
                    className: "bg-white text-temple-brown hover:bg-gray-100",
                    onClick: () => n == null ? void 0 : n(c.mostConnected.id),
                    children: "View Profile"
                })]
            })
        }), a.jsxs("div", {
            className: "space-y-4",
            children: [a.jsx("h3", {
                className: "text-xl font-semibold text-temple-brown",
                children: "Family Clusters"
            }), o.length > 0 ? a.jsx("div", {
                className: "grid gap-4",
                children: o.map( (u, d) => a.jsxs(re, {
                    className: "p-6",
                    children: [a.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "flex items-start justify-between mb-4",
                        children: [a.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [a.jsxs("h4", {

                            }), a.jsxs("div", {
                                className: "flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2",
                                children: [a.jsxs("span", {
                                    className: "flex items-center",

                                        className: "mr-1",
                                        size: 14
                                    }), u.members.length, " members"]
                                }), a.jsxs("span", {

                                        size: 14
                                    }), u.connections, " connections"]
                                }), a.jsxs("span", {

                                        size: 14
                                    }), u.generations, " generations"]
                                })]
                            })]
                        }), a.jsxs(xt, {
                            variant: "secondary",
                            className: "bg-saffron-100 text-saffron-800",
                            children: [u.members.length, " Members"]
                        })]
                    }), a.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-3 mb-4",
                        children: [u.members.slice(0, 6).map(f => a.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "flex items-center space-x-3 p-3 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg cursor-pointer hover:bg-gray-100 transition-colors",
                            onClick: () => n == null ? void 0 : n(f.id),
                            children: [a.jsx("div", {
                                className: "w-8 h-8 bg-saffron-200 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center",

                                    className: "text-temple-brown",
                                    size: 14
                                })
                            }), a.jsxs("div", {
                                className: "flex-1 min-w-0",
                                children: [a.jsx("p", {
                                    className: "font-medium text-sm truncate",
                                    children: f.fullName
                                }), a.jsxs("p", {
                                    className: "text-xs text-gray-500 truncate",
                                    children: [f.currentCity, ", ", f.currentState]
                                })]
                            })]
                        }, f.id)), u.members.length > 6 && a.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "flex items-center justify-center p-3 bg-gray-100 rounded-lg text-sm text-gray-600",
                            children: ["+", u.members.length - 6, " more members"]
                        })]
                    }), a.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [a.jsx("h5", {
                            className: "font-medium text-temple-brown mb-2",
                            children: "Geographic Distribution"
                        }), a.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "flex flex-wrap gap-2",
                            children: [u.locations.slice(0, 5).map( (f, m) => a.jsxs(xt, {
                                variant: "outline",
                                className: "text-xs",
                                children: [a.jsx(Pt, {
                                    className: "mr-1",
                                    size: 10
                                }), f]
                            }, m)), u.locations.length > 5 && a.jsxs(xt, {
                                variant: "outline",
                                className: "text-xs",
                                children: ["+", u.locations.length - 5, " more"]
                            })]
                        })]
                    })]
                }, u.id))
            }) : a.jsxs(re, {
                className: "p-8 text-center",
                children: [a.jsx(wo, {
                    className: "mx-auto mb-4 text-gray-400",
                    size: 48
                }), a.jsx("h3", {
                    className: "text-lg font-semibold text-gray-600 mb-2",
                    children: "No Family Clusters Found"
                }), a.jsx("p", {
                    className: "text-gray-500",
                    children: "Start adding family relationships to see network analysis"
                })]
            })]
        }), a.jsxs(re, {
            className: "p-6",
            children: [a.jsx("h3", {
                className: "text-lg font-semibold text-temple-brown mb-4",
                children: "Relationship Distribution"
            }), a.jsx("div", {
                className: "grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-3",
                children: Object.entries(c.byType).map( ([u,d]) => a.jsxs("div", {

                    }), a.jsx("div", {
                        className: "text-sm text-gray-600",
                        children: u
                    })]
                }, u))
            })]
        })]
    })
}
function L8({member: e, relationships: t, allMembers: n, allRelationships: r, onMemberClick: s}) {
    const {t: i} = Vt()
      , {transformRelationshipType: l, transformMemberData: o} = ha()
      , c = h => ({
        Parents: "bg-blue-600 text-white border-blue-700",
        Spouse: "bg-pink-600 text-white border-pink-700",
        Children: "bg-green-600 text-white border-green-700",

        "Grand Children": "bg-teal-600 text-white border-teal-700",

    })[h] || "bg-gray-400 text-white border-gray-500"
      , u = h => h === "Male" ? "bg-blue-50 border-blue-200 text-blue-900" : h === "Female" ? "bg-pink-50 border-pink-200 text-pink-900" : "bg-gray-50 border-gray-200 text-gray-900"
      , d = [{
        name: "Parents",
        types: ["Father", "Mother", "Step Father", "Step Mother"]
    }, {
        name: "Spouse",
        types: ["Wife", "Husband"]
    }, {

    }, {

    }, {

    }]
      , f = d.reduce( (h, g) => {
        const y = t.filter(b => g.types.includes(b.relationshipType));
        return y.length > 0 && (h[g.name] = y),
        h
    }
    , {})
      , m = t.filter(h => !d.some(g => g.types.includes(h.relationshipType)));
    return m.length > 0 && (f["Other Family Connections"] || (f["Other Family Connections"] = []),
    f["Other Family Connections"].push(...m)),
    a.jsxs("div", {

            className: `p-6 ${e.gender === "Male" ? "bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-500 to-blue-600" : e.gender === "Female" ? "bg-gradient-to-r from-pink-500 to-pink-600" : "bg-gradient-to-r from-saffron-500 to-gold-500"} text-white`,

                children: [a.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex items-center space-x-4",
                    children: [a.jsx("div", {
                        className: `w-16 h-16 ${e.gender === "Male" ? "bg-blue-50" : e.gender === "Female" ? "bg-pink-50" : "bg-white"} rounded-full flex items-center justify-center overflow-hidden`,

                            src: e.profilePicture,

function Qb({member: e, relationships: t}) {
    const [n,r] = p.useState(!1)
      , [s,i] = p.useState(!1)
      , [l,o] = p.useState("")
      , {toast: c} = qr()
      , u = async () => {
        i(!0);
        try {
            const h = [{
                name: "Parents",
                types: ["Father", "Mother", "Step Father", "Step Mother"]
            }, {
                name: "Spouse",
                types: ["Wife", "Husband"]
            }, {
                name: "Children",
                types: ["Son", "Daughter", "Step-Son", "Step-Daughter"]
            }, {
                name: "Siblings",
                types: ["Elder Brother", "Elder Sister", "Younger Brother", "Younger Sister", "Step-Brother", "Step-Sister"]
            }, {
                name: "Grand Parents",
                types: ["Paternal Grandfather", "Paternal Grandmother", "Maternal Grandfather", "Maternal Grandmother"]
            }, {
                name: "Grand Children",
                types: ["Grand Daughter -Son Side", "Grand Son-Son Side", "Grand Daughter -Daughter Side", "Grand Son-Daughter Side"]
            }, {
                name: "In-Laws",
                types: ["Mother-in-Law", "Father-in-Law", "Brother-in-Law", "Sister-in-Law", "Son-in-Law", "Daughter-in-Law"]
            }, {
                name: "Cousins",
                types: ["Cousin Brother-Father Side", "Cousin Sister-Father Side", "Cousin Brother-Mother Side", "Cousin Sister-Mother Side"]
            }, {
                name: "Aunts & Uncles",
                types: ["Aunt-Father Side", "Uncle-Father Side", "Aunt-Mother Side", "Uncle-Mother Side"]
            }, {
                name: "Other Family Connections",
                types: ["Nephew", "Niece"]
            }]
              , g = {};
            h.forEach(w => {
                const C = t.filter(j => w.types.includes(j.relationshipType));
                C.length > 0 && (g[w.name] = C)
            }
            );
            const y = new Date().toLocaleDateString("en-US", {
                year: "numeric",
                month: "long",
                day: "numeric"
            });
            let b = `# Family Story of ${e.fullName}

`;
            b += `*Generated on ${y}*

`,
            b += `## Personal Information
`,
            b += `**Full Name:** ${e.fullName}
`,
            b += `**Gender:** ${e.gender || "Not specified"}
`,
            b += `**Marital Status:** ${e.maritalStatus || "Not specified"}
`,
            b += `**Birth Place:** ${e.birthCity}, ${e.birthState}, ${e.birthCountry}
`,
            b += `**Current Location:** ${e.currentCity}, ${e.currentState}, ${e.currentCountry}
`,
            e.phone && (b += `**Phone:** ${e.phone}
`),
            e.email && (b += `**Email:** ${e.email}
`),
            e.fatherName && (b += `**Father's Name:** ${e.fatherName}
`),
            e.motherName && (b += `**Mother's Name:** ${e.motherName}
`),
            e.spouseName && (b += `**Spouse's Name:** ${e.spouseName}
`),
            b += `
## Family Connections

`,
            b += `${e.fullName} has ${t.length} family connection${t.length === 1 ? "" : "s"} recorded in our family registry.

`,
            Object.entries(g).forEach( ([w,C]) => {
                b += `### ${w}

`,
                C.forEach(j => {
                    const S = j.relatedMember;
                    b += `**${S.fullName}** *(${j.relationshipType})*
`,
                    S.currentCity && S.currentState && (b += `- Location: ${S.currentCity}, ${S.currentState}
`),
                    S.phone && (b += `- Phone: ${S.phone}
`),
                    S.email && (b += `- Email: ${S.email}
`),
                    S.maritalStatus && (b += `- Marital Status: ${S.maritalStatus}
`),
                    S.spouseName && (b += `- Spouse: ${S.spouseName}
`),
                    b += `
`
                }
                )
            }
            ),
            b += `## Family Statistics

`,
            b += `- **Total Family Members:** ${t.length}
`,
            b += `- **Relationship Types:** ${new Set(t.map(w => w.relationshipType)).size}
`,
            b += `- **Family Locations:** ${new Set(t.map(w => `${w.relatedMember.currentCity}, ${w.relatedMember.currentState}`)).size}
`;
            const x = t.filter(w => w.relatedMember.gender === "Male").length
              , v = t.filter(w => w.relatedMember.gender === "Female").length;
            b += `- **Male Family Members:** ${x}
`,
            b += `- **Female Family Members:** ${v}
`,
            b += `
## Family Tree Overview

`,
            b += `This family story represents the comprehensive family network of ${e.fullName}, `,
            b += `documenting ${t.length} family relationships across multiple generations and locations. `,
            b += `The family network spans across various cities and states, creating a rich tapestry of connections.

`,
            g.Parents && (b += `The foundation of this family tree begins with ${e.fullName}'s parents: `,
            b += g.Parents.map(w => w.relatedMember.fullName).join(" and ") + ". "),
            g.Spouse && (b += `${e.fullName} is married to ${g.Spouse[0].relatedMember.fullName}. `),
            g.Children && (b += `The family continues with ${g.Children.length} children: `,
            b += g.Children.map(w => w.relatedMember.fullName).join(", ") + ". "),
            g.Siblings && (b += `${e.fullName} has ${g.Siblings.length} sibling${g.Siblings.length === 1 ? "" : "s"}: `,
            b += g.Siblings.map(w => w.relatedMember.fullName).join(", ") + ". "),
            b += `

---

`,
            b += `*This family story was generated from the Sri Lakshmi Temple Family Registry on ${y}.*
`,
            b += "*For updates or corrections, please contact the temple administration.*",
            o(b),
            c({
                title: "Family Story Generated",
                description: "Your family story has been successfully generated!"
            })
        } catch (h) {
            console.error("Error generating family story:", h),
            c({
                title: "Error",
                description: "Failed to generate family story. Please try again.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        } finally {
            i(!1)
        }
    }
      , d = async () => {
        try {
            await navigator.clipboard.writeText(l),
            c({
                title: "Copied to Clipboard",
                description: "Family story has been copied to your clipboard!"
            })
        } catch {
            c({
                title: "Error",
                description: "Failed to copy to clipboard.",
                variant: "destructive"
            })
        }
    }
      , f = () => {
        const h = new Blob([l],{
            type: "text/markdown"
        })
          , g = URL.createObjectURL(h)
          , y = document.createElement("a");
        y.href = g,
        y.download = `${e.fullName.replace(/\s+/g, "_")}_Family_Story.md`,
        document.body.appendChild(y),
        y.click(),
        document.body.removeChild(y),
        URL.revokeObjectURL(g),
        c({
            title: "Download Started",
            description: "Your family story file is being downloaded!"
        })
    }
      , m = async () => {
        if (navigator.share)
            try {
                await navigator.share({
                    title: `Family Story of ${e.fullName}`,
                    text: l
                })
            } catch {
                d()
            }
        else
            d()
    }
    ;
    return a.jsxs(Yt, {
        open: n,
        onOpenChange: r,
        children: [a.jsx(Ka, {
            asChild: !0,
            children: a.jsxs(J, {
                variant: "outline",
                className: "bg-gradient-to-r from-saffron-500 to-gold-500 hover:from-saffron-600 hover:to-gold-600 text-white border-0",
                children: [a.jsx(Iu, {
                    className: "mr-2",
                    size: 16
                }), "Export Family Story"]
            })
        }), a.jsxs(Qt, {
            className: "max-w-4xl max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto",
            children: [a.jsx(Zt, {
                children: a.jsx(Xt, {
                    className: "text-xl font-bold text-temple-brown",
                    children: "Family Story Export"
                })
            }), a.jsxs("div", {
                className: "space-y-6",
                children: [a.jsxs(re, {
                    className: "bg-gradient-to-r from-saffron-50 to-gold-50 border-saffron-200",
                    children: [a.jsx(ln, {

    interpolate(t, n, r, s) {

          , u = g => {

    nest(t, n, r={}) {

                })

            c
